I often question this kind of question with my OCs. A lot of people may hear about the death of some oc, but they would not be sad. Whereas some death may not be well known, but people grieve on their death a lot more.

Finding Suviara, a mythical land often appears in video games and fairytales. He and his friends would go to churches and historical places and find ‘clues’ about it. Of course, nothing he found is real evidence but just very vague mention of it

And Habio is the unifier of the group. He rarely follows rules. He is almost the opposite of Yume. ‘Rules are not always fair. If you know it’s not fair, why would you follow it?’ is what he says. Habio is a gamer and athlete boi who dreams of https://t.co/UQRVzTAuHH

Yume is a very strict person. He will follow every rules and laws strictly and will warn anyone who is breaking them. For him rules are rules and no matter who you are, you have to abide them. ‘That’s the only way society and go further’ as he says. https://t.co/AMAYudyYmo

With Fateranis, God of Wisdom, and also Desloir, Goddess of Death. While Yume feel more connected with Nerime, Goddess of Light. 
But overall Miji more of a believer than Yume, since he actually wants to become a priest in the future

Miji loves spending time with his friends but he also enjoy being alone. Until his thoughts start to get out of control, then he would immediately visit a friend (most of the time Yume) but now that Sefal is in town he also visit him often. Miji feels connected https://t.co/a1UdNV9F0B

They are both the invisible kid of the class (Yume is a member of student council and knows quite a lot of people) but one is fine with one does not.

Even if I have to take a break some days or even if I have to work for jobs that will leave me with an hour of free time daily, I will still find a time to draw my comic. As long as I’m still breathing, I will never stop doing what I love the most
While many may think my dream is childish (and sometimes I agree with that myself) I will still continue to draw and write the story I’ve been creating since I was a child.

It’s not going to be easy and you will fail and fail, and you will be doing things you don’t enjoy in order to achieve it. I don’t have many dreams growing up, I only know that I want to pursue my story and make my characters known.

It makes me so sad when someone so passionate about decided to give up drawing wholly because it doesn’t make enough for a living. It is a sad truth that people in the creative fields have to face, but I believe that with strong passion dedication, we can achieve anything.
